According to the Meta IPMI OEM command spec, 

We should get the response data index 12, which represents GPIO 8 to GPIO15.

It means PWRGD_SYS_PWROK_INDEX=12.

(Response from IPMB request using  shell script: 
Index 1 : Data Format (yyyyay)
Index 2 : status 
Index 3 : NetFn
Index 4 : lun
Index 5 : cmd
Index 6 : cc code
Index 7 : data size
Index 8-N : IPMI response data)
